editorialNotes.tagline: New ways to sketch and animate
editorialNotes.standard: With stunning filters and thousands of importable brushes, this app lets you generate high-calibre artwork at a blistering pace. It supports pressure sensitivity and Apple Pencil–as well as iCloud Drive–so sharing your work is incredibly simple.
editorialNotes.short: This super-intuitive app makes it simple to paint your next masterpiece.
Learn to read and pronounce words with your new friend!
editorialNotes.tagline: Learn to read with a friend

ios.subtitle: Best Stalker IPTV App with EPG

editorialNotes.standard: Everyone needs a task manager—and Things is adaptable enough for anyone. This Apple Design Award winner is crisp and lightweight, featuring a simple but effective interface. The ever-present Magic Plus button makes it easy to add to-do’s from anywhere in the app, and organising items is as simple as dragging them where you want them. It’s like the unicorn of productivity tools: deep enough for serious work, surprisingly easy to use, and gorgeous enough to enjoy staring at.
editorialNotes.short: Organize class projects, assignments and daily to-do lists.

editorialNotes.standard: With a suite of powerful tools, touch-screen controls, gorgeous templates, and customizable effects, this full-featured editor is in a class of its own. Plus, with iCloud Drive, you can edit on your iPhone, iPad, or Mac, wherever you are.
editorialNotes.short: Make your pictures shine with this set of photography tools.

name: Little Kitten My Pet Kitty Cat

editorialNotes.tagline: Holiday fun with a festive feline
editorialNotes.standard: The moment we met wee kitty Crumbs in Little Kitten, we let out an audible “awww.” This adorable digital feline encourages children to play and explore, interacting with the lively toys and simple games in Crumbs’ room. We’re amazed by the cinematic animation, and appreciate the sleep timer that sends Crumbs to bed when our kids’ screen time is over.
editorialNotes.short: Embark on exciting adventures with your own kitty pal.

editorialNotes.standard: Nothing beats a kid-friendly game that keeps the whole family captivated—and Toca has us snipping, straightening, and styling to our heart's content. Once we've perfected our customer's silly new ‘dos, we make sure to add some accessories, snap a pic, and share the hair.

name: Montessori French Syllables - learn to read French words in a fun lab setting

editorialNotes.standard: Kids (and kids at heart) can unleash their inner scientists with this captivatingly clever robot-creation kit, which features millions of different combinations for mechanical inventions. Whether you’re assembling a wheeled bot with laser guns for arms or a jolly jumping automaton with pogo-stick legs, taking your new bot on a walk through the woods will highlight the success—or the rough edges—of your design. While The Robot Factory teaches some nifty physics basics, we like to play around just for the pure fun of it.
editorialNotes.short: Design and experiment with all types of robots.

name: TV Cast Pro for Fire TV

editorialNotes.short: Elevate your creativity through colourful caleidoscopic designs.

name: Star Walk 2 Pro: Night Sky Map

editorialNotes.short: Powerful astronomy toolkit to screen the night sky.

ios.subtitle: Build up a farm & grow veggies

editorialNotes.standard: Even a kid can run Dr. Panda’s farm, and ours love being in charge. Who wouldn’t? Milking cows, gathering honey, making jam—it’s easy to figure out and fun selling food to unlock new activities. Plus, the papercraft-style animals couldn’t be more adorable.
editorialNotes.short: Grow wheat, collect milk, and make bread on your own farm.

ios.subtitle: The night and low light camera

editorialNotes.short: A perfect app for taking pictures in low-light environments.
